                                        <assignee username="cpoerschke">Christine Poerschke</assignee>
                                    <reporter username="cpoerschke">Christine Poerschke</reporter>
                        <labels>
                    </labels>
                <created>Mon, 26 Jun 2017 14:28:36 +0000</created>
                <updated>Tue, 17 Oct 2017 11:03:29 +0000</updated>
                            <resolved>Wed, 5 Jul 2017 11:10:22 +0000</resolved>
                                                    <fixVersion>7.1</fixVersion>
                    <fixVersion>8.0</fixVersion>
                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>3</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16066822" author="cpoerschke" created="Wed, 28 Jun 2017 16:34:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching simpler alternative patch, getCore() returning null can be avoided by calling getSchema() instead.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Background/Context:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;How might the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/lucene-solr/blob/master/solr/core/src/java/org/apache/solr/search/SolrCoreParser.java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;SolrCoreParser&lt;/a&gt; be used &lt;em&gt;without&lt;/em&gt; a SolrCore you might ask?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;SolrCoreParser extends the Lucene &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/lucene-solr/blob/master/lucene/queryparser/src/java/org/apache/lucene/queryparser/xml/CoreParser.java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;CoreParser&lt;/a&gt; i.e. the core part of the name has nothing to do with solr cores.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.flax.co.uk/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Flax&lt;/a&gt;&apos;s &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/flaxsearch/luwak/blob/master/README.md&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Luwak&lt;/a&gt; has a &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/flaxsearch/luwak/blob/master/luwak/src/main/java/uk/co/flax/luwak/MonitorQueryParser.java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;MonitorQueryParser&lt;/a&gt; interface and a &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/flaxsearch/luwak/blob/master/luwak/src/main/java/uk/co/flax/luwak/queryparsers/LuceneQueryParser.java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;LuceneQueryParser&lt;/a&gt; implementation of that interface.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;If a MonitorQueryParser implementation used the SolrCoreParser then it might do so &lt;em&gt;without&lt;/em&gt; a SolrCore (but with an IndexSchema and a SolrResourceLoader).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
